When executing shell commands on this Windows system:
- Use `cmd /c "command"` syntax instead of bash syntax
- Do NOT use `&&` to chain commands in PowerShell. Use `; ` or wrap in `cmd /c "cmd1 && cmd2"`
- Use `cd /d "path"` for changing directories in cmd
- The default shell is PowerShell which does not support `&&` in older versions
- For git commands, run them directly without cd since the working directory is already the project root
